The paper deals with external memory data structures, which are typically studied in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The priority queue problem is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms, and is often studied in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The use of disk block size and main memory size suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. The lower bound proof is done in the cell probe model, which is a common model for studying data structures and algorithms, and thus the paper may also be relevant to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes algorithms and analyzes their performance, which falls under the cs.AL (Algorithms) sub-category.
